raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "python-openid" %}
{% set version = "2.2.5" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: "{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz"
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 92c51c3ecec846cbec4aeff11f9ff47303d4a63f93b0e6ac0ec02a091fed70ef

build:
  skip: True  # [py3k]
  number: 1000
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vvv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - openid
    - openid.consumer
    - openid.extensions
    - openid.extensions.draft
    - openid.server
    - openid.store
    - openid.yadis

about:
  home: http://github.com/openid/python-openid
  license: Apache 2.0
  license_file: LICENSE
  license_family: Apache
  summary: 'OpenID support for servers and consumers.'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - pmlandwehr
